oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Slide Collection - Sulphur Dell Baseball Park
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Home of the Nashville Vols, Sulphur Dell baseball park opened in 1870 and closed in 1963. The park was given its name because of a sulphur spring that ran through the area near the present location of the Bicentennial Mall. Sulphur Dell was demolished in 1966. 35 mm
